The paper focuses on optimizing locomotion controllers, which is a problem in robotics. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses Bayesian Optimization and a neural network, which are both machine learning techniques, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses learning an informed distance metric, which is a common problem in computer vision, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. The paper also involves optimization and control, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.SY (Systems and Control).
